    "There is a well-known relation between principal angles and SVD.",
    "Let U and V be basis of U and V respectively.",
    "It can be seen that all the singular values of U ⊤ V belong to [0, 1].",
    "Moreover, the principle angles defined above are just the arc-cosine of these singular values (Björck and Golub, 1973).",
    "For convenience of this work, we refer to the singular values of U ⊤ V as principal angles (instead of the arc-cosine of them)."
